hopobject.body: Who would I report to? trimethoprim sulfamethoxazole cvs It’s a total delight to see such ambitious kids’ theatre. This is probing, playful stuff and Ellen McDougall’s production makes its audience co-conspirators. The non-literal staging — where balloons stand in for soldiers — demands our help to build its story, while Zaza’s searching eyes seem to ask our advice throughout. There are swordfights, explosions and a healthy dose of messy chaos to boot. “That was sick,” gasped one young voice (which is slang for cool, these days).
